President Uhuru Kenyatta has blasted his deputy William Ruto accusing him of misleading and radicalizing young people instead of supporting&nbsp;government programs that will offer what he called realistic opportunities for the youth. In availed support for estranged NASA principals Raila Odinga and Kalonzo Musyoka, the president said, unlike his deputy, the two are speaking his language, giving the clearest indication that Ruto is nowhere on the president&rsquo;s succession plans.
